<task id="DEVOPS-021" project="Spaarke DevOps Project Tracking r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Backfill active projects via /devops-project-register</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~15 minutes</actual-effort>
    <completed>2026-06-23</completed>
    <tags>backfill, devops-project-register, rate-limit</tags>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Run `/devops-project-register --from-folder` for each ACTIVE project from the enumeration list (task 020). Per NFR-05, batch operations: groups of 20 with exponential backoff on 429. After this task: every active worktree has a matching Project Issue with all 6 new fields populated.
  </prompt>

  <role>Operations engineer comfortable with rate-limit hygiene. You batch + back off; you do not hammer the API.</role>

  <goal>
Every project on the task 020 ACTIVE list has a Project Issue on Project #2 with Parent Epic correct + all 6 new fields populated. Active projects view item count matches enumeration count.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-05">≤5000/hr REST, ≤5000 points/hr GraphQL; batch in groups of 20 with exponential backoff on 429</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15">Per F4: ordering by Epic then most-recent commit activity</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Idempotent — re-running on already-registered project is no-op</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/notes/backfill-enumeration-{date}.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/devops-project-register/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check">Confirm task 020 enumeration list is reviewed + Epic mappings confirmed (no remaining `[REVIEW]` markers).</step>
    <step order="1" name="Batch in groups of 20">Process projects in chunks of 20. Between chunks, sleep 5 seconds.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Per-project register">For each project: invoke `/devops-project-register --from-folder projects/{name} --epic #E`. Capture exit status + Issue URL. On 429, exponentially back off (initial 30s, double on repeat).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Failure tracking">Collect per-project failures into `notes/backfill-failures-{date}.md`. Continue with remaining projects.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify">After all batches: query `gh project item-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev` for `Type=Project` count. Compare against task 020 enumeration count.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Spot-check">Open Project #2 in browser; filter to Active projects view; spot-check 5 random Issues — Parent Epic + all 6 fields populated.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Failure remediation">For each failure: attempt individual re-run (skills are idempotent). Document any persistent failures.</step>
    <step order="7" name="README pointer block backfill">Verify each registered project has the `> **Portfolio**:` pointer block in its `README.md`. `/devops-project-register` should write this; spot-check 5 projects.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Skill">/devops-project-register</tool>
    <tool name="gh">Verification queries</tool>
    <tool name="sleep">Backoff</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="report">projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/notes/backfill-results-{date}.md</output>
    <output type="config">~20-30 new Project Issues on Project #2</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Project Issue created for every ACTIVE project from task 020 enumeration</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each Issue has Parent Epic + all 6 fields populated</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Spot-check of 5 random projects: README pointer block present</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No rate-limit failures unrecoverable (final state matches enumeration)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
